window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>The instant <i>New York Times </i>Best Seller</p> <p><b>One of </b><b><i>Newsweek</i></b><b>'s Most Anticipated Books of 2020</b></p> <p><b>One of </b><b><i>SheReads</i></b><b>' Most Anticipated Books of 2020</b></p> <p><b>One of </b><b><i>PopSugar</i></b><b>'s Most Anticipated Books of 2020</b></p> <p><b>One of </b><b><i>HelloGiggles</i></b><b>' Most Anticipated Books of 2020</b></p> <p><b>One of </b><b><i>Marie Claire</i></b><b>'s Best Fiction by Women in 2020</b></p> <p><b>One of </b><b><i>Womanâ€™s Day'</i></b><b>s Best Fiction Books Coming Out in 2020</b></p> <p>The electrifying number one <i>New York Times</i> best-selling authors of <i>The Wife Between Us</i> and <i>An Anonymous Girl</i> return with a brand new novel of psychological suspense, <b><i>You Are Not Alone</i></b>.</p> <p>Shay Miller wants to find love, but it eludes her. She wants to be fulfilled, but her job is a dead end. She wants to belong, but her life is increasingly lonely.</p> <p>Until Shay meets the Moore sisters. Cassandra and Jane live a life of glamorous perfection, and always get what they desire. When they invite Shay into their circle, everything seems to get better. Shay would die for them to like her. She may have to.&nbsp;</p> <p><b>A Macmillan Audio production from St. Martin's Press</b></p>"; 
